chao1995:
@Ziflin 

Cannot read property 'config' of undefined

In url_for.js, there is a line var config = this.config; where this is referring to the global context where the global variable config is defined.
So basically instead using hexo.extend.helper.store['url_for'](path), you need to 
* grab a reference to the global context using var globalContext = this when this is still referring to the global context. Using the script I am working on as an example to show where to place the line,
```javascript
function hierarchicalCategoryListHelper(...) {
    var globalContext = this; // you can start using globalContext below
}
hexo.extend.helper.register('hierarchicalCategoryList', function() {
    return hierarchicalCategoryListHelper(...);
});
``
* Then you can usehexo.extend.helper.store['url_for'].call(globalContext, path)`, there should be no error.
.

