. Found a solution by cnotethegr8 in a Stack Overflow discussion:
Create ignore_files_for_posts.js in themes/your-theme/scripts/ with this content:
```
hexo.extend.filter.register('after_init', function () {
  // Remove json / js files being inserted to db.json -> Pages
var listSync = hexo.extend.renderer.list(true),
      listAsync = hexo.extend.renderer.list();
delete listSync.json;
  delete listAsync.json;
  delete listSync.js;
  delete listAsync.js;
});
```
All .js-files / .json-files will be ignored. Can also be used for htm, html, css, js, json, swig, yml, yaml.
.

