I still have to check exclude in detail, but here's my point of view for now.
* skip_render: It check whether a file(md, ejs, html) should be rendered to html. This will just exclude file from rendering (into layout via hexo's templating system). The file will still be generated as it is and will be available in the generated site. You can use it if you have a html file and you want to use the file as it is(like a standalone file).


exclude: I think it checks files in source folder and decides whether to process files/dirs or not depending on the values of exclude, but the files are still read and  their data(hash, modified time...) is stored in db.json file. They are skipped from being processed and will not be available in the generated site.


ignore: It is to ignore directories that are not useful inside both source, theme folder. It acts very early when box(the processor) reads all files from source and theme directories. The file will be completely skipped.



Note, ignore ignores directories not files.
